Things to do here:
//CANIL Centre Welcome to the CANIL Harvest Centre Typically language courses are offered in this building
//David E. Enarson Gym Welcome to the David E. Enarson Gym The place where you should be every weekday from 11:00am - 11:30am. I.E. CHAPEL. Also used for HKIN courses and sports.
//Douglas Centre Welcome to the Douglas Centre TWUSA is based here. Also the lower cafe is just below.
//Douglas Hall Welcome to the Douglas Hall Dorms for any undergrad. Nice community
//Douglas Hall Welcome to the Ezra House A little portable used various functions. Quite cozy.
//Fosmark Centre Welcome to the Fosmark Some business course are held here from time to time. The Fosmark Centre was made in honour of two brothers, Carl and Lee Fosmark.
//Fraser Hall Welcome to the Fraser Hall Check some dorm rooms and play ping pong in the lounge
//Gym Portable Welcome to the Gym Portable Admire the architecture
//Larsen Artium Welcome to the Larsen Atrium This is a great place to study. Sometimes people even sleep here. The yearbook photos are taken here as well.
//Mattson Centre Welcome to the Mattson Centre If you hanve anything to discuss with the registrar this is the place to go
//McMillan Hall Welcome to the McMillan Hall Housing for upperclassman.
//Music Building Welcome to the Music Building Some education and english class are held here but mainly this is where all music courses will be held.
//Neufeld Science Centre Welcome to the Neufeld Science Centre If your major has anyting to do with Math or Science; You Will Practically Live In This Building.
//Northwest Building Welcome to the Northwest Building All girls housing, also the main building for the business department.
//Reimer Student Centre Welcome to the Reimer Student Centre Located next to main cafe. If you have anything to discuss as of student issues or housing issues you come here.
//Robert N. Thompson Building Welcome to the Robert N. Thompson Building Home of the Theatre and English department
//Robson Hall Welcome to the Robson Hall Another upperclassman housing building. But there is an underground parking lot for this one.
//Vernon Strombeck Centre Welcome to the Vernon Strombeck Centre Pretty much only education majors know what the inside of this building looks like
//Welcome Centre Welcome to the Welcome Centre Any parking issues are resolved here
